{# Payroll-absent explanation panel — no source_ids to drill into.

  The detector fires when the statement covers ≥21 days with revenue
  ≥$50k AND no payroll-processor activity is found. The card's
  description states the rule; this panel surfaces the concrete period
  and revenue figure plus the operator playbook (1099-only is plausible;
  W-2 claims without payroll trace is a red flag).

  Inputs:
    - card: PatternCard
    - analysis: AnalysisRow (optional; period dates + true_revenue used in copy)
#}
<div class="evidence evidence-explanation">
  {% if analysis is defined and analysis and analysis.statement_period_start and analysis.statement_period_end %}
    <p>
      No payroll-processor activity found across
      <strong>{{ analysis.statement_period_start.strftime('%b %d') }} – {{ analysis.statement_period_end.strftime('%b %d, %Y') }}</strong>
      ({{ (analysis.statement_period_end - analysis.statement_period_start).days + 1 }} days).
      {% if analysis.true_revenue %}
        Revenue total <strong>{{ analysis.true_revenue | money }}</strong> qualifies for the payroll expectation (≥ $50k floor).
      {% endif %}
    </p>
  {% else %}
    <p>No payroll-processor activity found over the statement period.</p>
  {% endif %}
  <p>
    Today's review: ask the merchant how they pay employees / contractors.
    1099-only is a plausible explanation; <em>W-2 claims without payroll trace is a red flag</em>.
  </p>
</div>
